               SURE THAT THIS VALUE IS CONSISTENT WITH THAT OF L_INIT_M IN THE
               INCLUDE FILE.

    S_O    = VALUE OF THE SPIN-ORBIT COMPONENT SELECTED AS THE INITIAL STATE
               (EX. : 3/2, 5/2, ...)
               (=0) : THE FULL CORE STATE IS TAKEN INTO ACCOUNT

    ISELRULE  = SWITCH TO SELECT THE CHANNELS IN THE FINAL STATE:
                L-CUT-OFF OF THE COULOMB POTENTIAL EXPANSION

    I_SO   = SWITCH CONTROLLING THE SPIN-ORBIT
               (=0) NO SPIN-ORBIT TAKEN INTO ACCOUNT
               (=1) ONLY THE COMPONENT 'S_O' IS TAKEN INTO ACCOUNT
               (=2) BOTH SPIN-ORBIT COMPONENTS ARE TAKEN INTO ACCOUNT







